'Cocamide MEA', or 'cocamide monoethanolamine', is a solid, off-white to tan
compound, often sold in flaked form. The solid melts to yield a pale yellow
viscous clear to amber liquid. It is a mixture of fatty acid amides which is
produced from the fatty acids in coconut oil when reacted with ethanolamine.
